# Release artifacts (ephemeral — upload to GitHub releases then delete)
*.tar.gz
*.tar.gz.asc
*.apk
*.deb
*.deb.asc

# GPG / OpenPGP key material — NEVER commit private keys or revocation certs.
# Live keys stay in ~/.gnupg (outside the repo); this is a belt-and-suspenders
# guard against a stray `gpg --export-secret-keys` landing in the working tree.
# Note: plain *.asc is intentionally NOT ignored — the PUBLIC signing key may be
# committed deliberately. Only private/secret/revocation material is blocked.
*.key
*.gpg
*.rev
*private*.asc
*secret*.asc

# Third-party audit PDFs (e.g. Recurity Labs Proton Pass report) — referenced by
# docs/AI_SECURITY_AUDIT.md but not redistributed in the repo. Keep local only.
docs/artefacts/*.pdf

# Crypto-review outreach draft — working document, used when asking the question.
# Kept local, never committed (repo is going public).
docs/CRYPTO_REVIEW_QUESTION.md
